name: dumpnwpass
tagline: Tool written in Ruby that dumps already entered network passwords when given root privileges.
body:
##CAN HAZ R00T??? KTHXBYE!!1!11!!
You **NEED** to run the script as root. Otherwise it won't be able to look into the files!

###Output looks like this:
network => pass
note: Don't delete this file! It's used internally to help with page regeneration.
